qas.question: What was the population of Guinea-Bissau in 1950?
What was the population of Guinea-Bissau in 2010?
What is the source of the population data?

answers.text: the 2010 revison of the UN World Population Prospects

qas.question: What percentage of the population was below the age of 15?
What percentage of the population was 65 or older?

context: According to <a2_0>the 2010 revison of the UN World Population Prospects<a2_0/>, Guinea-Bissau's population was <a1_0>1,515,000<a1_0/> in 2010, compared to <a0_0>518,000<a0_0/> in 1950. The proportion of the population below the age of 15 in 2010 was <a3_0>41.3%<a3_0/>, 55.4% were aged between 15 and 65 years of age, while <a4_0>3.3%<a4_0/> were aged 65 years or older.
